Looks like it's quite easy to tie into Provider / InheritedWidget also. Just need to pass in the context to the `initProperty` callback:
```
anim1 = initProperty((context, widget) {
      return StatefulAnimationController(
        duration: context.read<Duration>(),
        vsync: (widget as FooView).vsync,
      );
    });
```
This will manage the animation lifecycle, and properly sync to the `widget.vsync` or provided `Duration` changing.

