Finding lots of nice wins here. Because everything is stateful, it's just very easy to add syntactic sugar and the code is very familiar.

For example, if I add a couple small methods to the `AnimationProp`: 
```
  Animation<T> addTween<T>(Tween<T> tween, {Curve curve: Curves.linear}) {
    return tween.animate(CurvedAnimation(parent: _controller, curve: curve));
  }
  
  Animation<double> tweenDouble({double begin: 0.0, double end: 1.0, Curve curve: Curves.linear}) =>
      addTween(Tween<double>(begin: begin, end: end), curve: curve);

  Animation<int> tweenInt({int begin: 0, int end: 100, Curve curve: Curves.linear}) =>
      addTween(IntTween(begin: begin, end: end), curve: curve);
  ```
Then I can write some pretty tight animation code, all off the back of the one AnimationController:
```
class _SimpleAnimatedBtnState extends State<SimpleAnimatedBtn> with StatefulPropManagerMixin<SimpleAnimatedBtn> {
  Animation<double> fadeTween;
  Animation<int> countTween;
  Animation<Color> colorTween;

  void initState() {
    // Core anim that drives everything
    AnimationProp tapAnim = initProperty((widget, context){
      return AnimationProp(
         duration: (widget as SimpleAnimatedBtn).duration, 
         vsync: context.read<TickerProvider>());
    });
    // Use syntactic sugar to easily add some tween curves and settings
    fadeTween = tapAnim.tweenDouble(curve: Curves.easeOut, begin: .2, end: 1);
    countTween = tapAnim.tweenInt(curve: Curves.easeOut, begin: 90, end: 100);
    colorTween = tapAnim.addTween(ColorTween(begin: Colors.red, end: Colors.green));
    // Add gesture tap-detector in one line
    initProperty((_, __) => GestureProp(onTap: () => tapAnim.controller.forward(from: 0)));
    super.initState();
  }

  // Our build method is sparkling clean, it's actually just view code and layout logic (yay!)
  Widget statefulBuild(BuildContext context) {
    print("Build");
    String label = "${countTween.value}";
    Color fillColor = colorTween.value.withOpacity(fadeTween.value);
    return Container(
      decoration: BoxDecoration(color: fillColor),
      alignment: Alignment.center,
